
[1]trice

   TRICE, v.t. In seamen's language, to haul and tie up by means of a
   small rope or line.

   TRICE, n. A very short time; an instant; a moment.

   If they get never so great spoil at any time, they waste the same in a
   trice.

   A man shall make his fortune in a trice.
